net.jsoundsystem
Class JSound3D

java.lang.Object
  net.jsoundsystem.JSound
      net.jsoundsystem.JSound3D

public class JSound3D
extends JSound

An extension of the JSound class that simulates a 3D sound effect. 3D sounds have a listener position (the user) and a source position (the origin of the sound). A JSound3D will automatically update the loudness and the position of where the sound is played depending on the positions. The max distance from what sounds can be heard can be set by JSoundSystem.setMaxDistance() and the position of the listener can be set by JSoundSystem.setListenerPosition().

Note that currently this simulates a very shallow 3D effect and works more like sounds in two dimensional space. Also note that you cannot change the volume or panning of 3D sounds since this is automatically done by the JSoundSystem API

Author:
Johan Jansen
